# Workspace & Project Management Plan

## Current Implementation
- Boot script loads default workspace layout (Main.json) which assigns workspaces to monitors
- Boot script also loads projects onto each workspace from workspace_projects.json
- Projects can be loaded independently onto any workspace

## Workspace Layout Loading Logic (TO IMPLEMENT)

When loading a workspace layout (e.g., Main.json):
1. Check if there's a currently loaded workspace layout name stored somewhere (e.g., ~/.config/hypr/layouts/.current_workspace_layout)
2. Compare the name in the layout being loaded with the stored current layout name
3. If **different** (or no current layout exists):
   - Close ALL windows on ALL workspaces
   - Load the new workspace layout (assign workspaces to monitors)
   - Update the stored current layout name
   - Optionally: Load associated projects for each workspace
4. If **same**:
   - Do nothing (or just ensure workspaces are still on correct monitors)

## Project Loading Logic (TO IMPLEMENT LATER)

When loading a project onto a specific workspace:
- Close all windows on that specific workspace only
- Launch the project's windows on that workspace

## Storage Needed
- File to track currently loaded workspace layout name: `~/.config/hypr/layouts/.current_workspace_layout`
- This allows comparison to know if we're switching layouts or reloading the same one
